Scenario description This is the online testing scenario. You can use it to evaluate the classifiers trained in the previous step. Important :You will have to run the Classifier training scenario at least one in order to use the online testing application. Game rules The game is a simple shooter. You control a representation of a ship and your goal is to shoot at the appearing targets. There are three possible controls Turn clockwise, Turn counter-clockwise and Shoot corresponding to left, right and front flickering form.
Signal processing for the first stimulation frequency

Game Configuration There are two settings that you can change in this scenario: Target sequence : a list of positions on which the targets will appear. Each position is represented by a number from 0 to 7, representing the angle of the target. Ship angular speed : the angle (in radians) by which the ship will rotate every time it receives a command.
Signal processing for the third stimulation frequency
Signal processing for the second stimulation frequency

External Stimulator This SSVEP scenario needs to run along with an external application. The application is run automatically after the start of the scenario. The stimulator accepts two keyboard commands: Pressing <Space> will send a start stimulation to the scenario and the experiment will begin. Pressing <Escape> will quit the stimulator and stop the scenario.
